fromPort.description: Starting value for a range of allowed port numbers.

ipRange.description: Range of allowed IP addresses expressed in CIDR notationE.g., `000.000.000.000/[subnet mask]` or `0.0.0.0/[subnet mask]`.

protocol.description: Network communication protocol used by the fleetE.g., `TCP` or `UDP`

toPort.description: Ending value for a range of allowed port numbers. Port numbers are end-inclusive. This value must be higher than `from_port`.
